Citation.sTitle: Effect of temperature on the solvation of 15-crown-5 ether inwater ethanol and water propan-1-ol mixtures
Citation.sAbstract: The enthalpies of solution of 15-crown-5 (15C5) ether in water ethanol and water propan-1-ol mixtureshave been measured at 293.15 308.15 K. The relative importance of the solvation mechanism appearedto depend on co-solvent properties. The effect of temperature on the solvation process of 15C5 in themixtures of water with ethanol or propan-1-ol was discussed.
